In [22]:
model1 = ep.SISModel(G)

# Model Configuration
cfg = mc.Configuration()
cfg.add_model_parameter('beta', 0.1)                   # Infection probability     S -> I
cfg.add_model_parameter('lambda', 0.9)                  # Recovery probability      I -> S
cfg.add_model_parameter("fraction_infected", 0.05)     
model1.set_initial_status(cfg)

# Simulation 
iterations = model1.iteration_bunch(50)
trends = model1.build_trends(iterations)

# Show simulation
viz = DiffusionTrend(model1, trends)
viz.plot("diffusion.pdf")
DiffusionTrend.plot(viz)

#dynamic model

dg = dn.DynGraph()
for t in xrange(0,45):
    g = nx.random_geometric_graph(1000, 0.1, seed=896803)
    dg.add_interactions_from(g.edges(),t)
    

dmodel = dm.DynSISModel(dg)

# Model Configuration
cfg = mc.Configuration()
cfg.add_model_parameter('beta', 0.1)                   # Infection probability     S -> I
cfg.add_model_parameter('lambda', 0.9)                  # Recovery probability      I -> S
cfg.add_model_parameter("fraction_infected", 0.05)      
dmodel.set_initial_status(cfg)

# Simulation execution
#diterations = dmodel.execute_snapshots(45)
diterations = dmodel.execute_iterations()
dtrends = dmodel.build_trends(diterations)

# Show simulation
dviz = DiffusionTrend(dmodel, dtrends)
DiffusionTrend.plot(dviz)
